@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <p class="lead">Last Updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</p>

            <hr />

            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                Welcome to the Food Safety Inspection Tracker. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, 
                disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our application. Please read this privacy 
                policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this privacy policy, please do not access 
                the application.
            </p>

            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <h3>2.1 Personal Information</h3>
            <p>We collect the following personal information when you register and use our application:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Email address, username, and password (encrypted)</li>
                <li><strong>User Role:</strong> Admin, Inspector, or Viewer classification</li>
                <li><strong>Activity Logs:</strong> Login/logout timestamps, actions performed, and IP addresses</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.2 Inspection Data</h3>
            <p>We collect and store information related to food safety inspections:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Premises information (name, address, town, risk rating)</li>
                <li>Inspection records (date, score, outcome, notes)</li>
                <li>Follow-up information (due dates, status, closure dates)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.3 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Log Data:</strong> Application events, errors, and system activities via Serilog</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages accessed, features used, and session duration</li>
                <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> Browser type, device information, and operating system</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>To provide, operate, and maintain the Food Safety Inspection Tracker</li>
                <li>To manage user accounts and authentication</li>
                <li>To enforce role-based access control (Admin, Inspector, Viewer)</li>
                <li>To track and maintain inspection records and follow-ups</li>
                <li>To generate dashboard reports and analytics</li>
                <li>To maintain an audit trail for regulatory compliance</li>
                <li>To detect, prevent, and address technical issues and security threats</li>
                <li>To comply with legal obligations and food safety regulations</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
            <h3>4.1 Database</h3>
            <p>
                All data is stored in a secure SQLite database with encrypted connections. 
                Access is restricted to authorized personnel only.
            </p>

            <h3>4.2 Passwords</h3>
            <p>
                User passwords are hashed using ASP.NET Core Identity's secure hashing algorithms. 
                We never store passwords in plain text.
            </p>

            <h3>4.3 Logging</h3>
            <p>
                Application logs are stored in rotating daily files with restricted access. 
                Logs include user activities for audit trail purposes but exclude sensitive data 
                such as passwords.
            </p>

            <h3>4.4 Security Measures</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>HTTPS encryption for all data transmission</li>
                <li>Role-based access control (RBAC)</li>
                <li>Anti-forgery tokens to prevent CSRF attacks</li>
                <li>Input validation to prevent injection attacks</li>
                <li>Regular security updates and patches</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share information in the following circumstances:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law, court order, or government authority</li>
                <li><strong>Health Authorities:</strong> Food safety inspection data may be shared with relevant health authorities</li>
                <li><strong>Internal Use:</strong> Authorized administrators and inspectors within your organization</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>6. User Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data</li>
                <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your account (subject to legal retention requirements)</li>
                <li><strong>Export:</strong> Request export of your data in a portable format</li>
                <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to certain data processing activities</li>
            </ul>
            <p>To exercise these rights, please contact your system administrator.</p>

            <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain your information for as long as:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Your account is active</li>
                <li>Necessary to provide services to you</li>
                <li>Required by law (food safety records may have specific retention periods)</li>
                <li>Needed for audit trail and compliance purposes</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>8. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
            <p>
                Our application uses essential cookies for authentication and session management. 
                These cookies are necessary for the application to function properly and include:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Authentication Cookie:</strong> Maintains your login session</li>
                <li><strong>Anti-forgery Token:</strong> Protects against CSRF attacks</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We do not use tracking cookies or third-party analytics cookies.
            </p>

            <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>
                This application is not intended for use by children under the age of 18. 
                We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
            </p>

            <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify users of any 
                material changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the 
                "Last Updated" date.
            </p>

            <h2>11. Contact Information</h2>
            <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact:</p>
            <address>
                <strong>Food Safety Inspection Tracker - System Administrator</strong><br />
                Email: <a href="mailto:admin@foodsafety.local">admin@foodsafety.local</a><br />
                <br />
                <em>For technical issues or security concerns, please contact your IT department.</em>
            </address>

            <h2>12. Compliance</h2>
            <p>
                This application is designed to comply with:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) - for EU users</li>
                <li>Food Safety regulations and standards</li>
                <li>Local data protection laws</li>
            </ul>

            <hr />

            <div class="alert alert-info">
                <h4>Your Privacy Matters</h4>
                <p>
                    We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your data. 
                    This application uses industry-standard security measures and best practices to 
                    safeguard your information.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4">
                <a asp-action="Index" class="btn btn-primary">Return to Home</a>
                @if (User.Identity?.IsAuthenticated == true)
                {
                    <a asp-controller="Dashboard" asp-action="Index" class="btn btn-secondary">Go to Dashboard</a>
                }
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

